Class PodcastSocialInteract

java.lang.Object
com.apptasticsoftware.rssreader.module.podcast.PodcastSocialInteract
public class PodcastSocialInteract extends Object
Represents a social interaction point for a podcast episode or the podcast as a whole. This element specifies the "root post" of a comment thread that serves as the canonical location for comments and discussion. It can be considered the "official" social media comment space for the episode or podcast. <p>Multiple social interaction points can be specified, with priority determining the display order. The tag can also be used to disable public comments by using the "disabled" protocol value.

  • Method Details

    • getProtocol

      public String getProtocol()
      Gets the protocol used for interacting with the comment root post. A special value of "disabled" can be used to indicate that public comments should not be shown alongside the episode or podcast.
      Returns:
      The protocol name (required).

    • setProtocol

      public void setProtocol(String protocol)
      Sets the protocol used for interacting with the comment root post.
      Parameters:
      protocol - The protocol name (required). Use "disabled" to indicate that public comments should not be shown.

    • getUri

      public String getUri()
      Gets the URI/URL of the root post comment. For ActivityPub platforms (like Mastodon or Pleroma), it's recommended to use the URI value (fully-formed URL with a GUID) rather than the HTML page URL.
      Returns:
      The URI of the root post comment (required).

    • setUri

      public void setUri(String uri)
      Sets the URI/URL of the root post comment.
      Parameters:
      uri - The URI of the root post comment (required).

    • getAccountId

      public Optional<String> getAccountId()
      Gets the account identifier on the commenting platform.
      Returns:
      An Optional containing the account ID of the root post creator, or empty if not provided (recommended but optional).

    • setAccountId

      public void setAccountId(String accountId)
      Sets the account identifier on the commenting platform.
      Parameters:
      accountId - The account ID of the root post creator (recommended).

    • getAccountUrl

      public Optional<String> getAccountUrl()
      Gets the public URL of the account on the commenting platform.
      Returns:
      An Optional containing the account's public URL, or empty if not provided.

    • setAccountUrl

      public void setAccountUrl(String accountUrl)
      Sets the public URL of the account on the commenting platform.
      Parameters:
      accountUrl - The public URL of the account that created the root post.

    • getPriority

      public Optional<Integer> getPriority()
      Gets the display priority of this social interaction point. Lower numbers indicate higher priority. Used when multiple social interaction points are present to determine display order.
      Returns:
      An Optional containing the priority value, or empty if not specified.

    • setPriority

      public void setPriority(Integer priority)
      Sets the display priority of this social interaction point.
      Parameters:
      priority - The priority value (lower numbers mean higher priority). Used to determine display order when multiple social interaction points are present.
